# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  FurBook — Firebase Authentication Configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
#  SETUP STEPS
#  ───────────
#  1. Go to https://console.firebase.google.com
#  2. Create a new project (e.g. "furbook")
#  3. Click "Add app" → Web
#  4. Copy the config values below from the Firebase SDK snippet
#  5. Copy THIS file:  cp .env.example .env.local
#  6. Fill in your values in .env.local
#  7. In Firebase Console → Authentication → Sign-in method, enable:
#       ✅ Email/Password
#       ✅ Google
#       ⚠️  Facebook  (requires a Facebook Developer App)
#       ⚠️  Apple     (requires Apple Developer account)
#  8. Restart the dev server:  npm run dev
#
#  All values are public (they appear in your built JS bundle).
#  Firebase security is enforced via Security Rules, not by hiding these keys.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=
